  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**What happened**:\r\n\r\nThe `AllowedCSIDrivers` field was added to the PodSecurityPolicy API in v1.14, but was never implemented. Having that option unimplemented can give a false sense of security, as a user might _think_ they have restricted CSI driver options, but haven't actually done so.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nWhen PodSecurityPolicy is enabled, no pods should be able to be created with an inline CSI driver unless explicitly allowed through this field.\r\n\r\nImplementing this is a hard requirement for bringing `CSIInlineVolume` to beta: https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/issues/596\r\n\r\n/sig storage auth\r\n/assign vladimirvivien\r\n/cc jsafrane msau liggitt\r\n/priority important-soon",
